Here is a lovely picture of me, Bid and Peter Astor, taken by Izumi Nakatani just after we arrived in Tokyo. We are sitting in a joint called Mister Donut. We think we look like three riverboat gamblers trying to look as though we had never, ever played poker before, no sir.
"Pat was good today. Short, 40 minutes. I wanted to hear the song of the Jazz Butcher more."
A couple of shots of Bid from the Monochrome Set having a wee jam with me at the soundcheck at Club 251. For what it's worth, he pays lead rather like a certain Max Eider...
They also appear to have kidnapped Izumi and force-fed her a decent chunk of Stockholm Syndrome Cake.
As you see, the riverboat gamblers have dropped all pretence of being anything other than crazed hooligans aflame with the urge to filthy lucre.
Me and Peter Astor photographed in the street by a Pete Astor fan who was literally shaking with excitement, bless him. - I think he thought I was Pete's bodyguard!
